project.description: Intergrates the Chipmunk physics system into Kiwi.js.

cp.Body.name: cp.Body
cp.Body.description:
Chipmunk's rigid body type. Rigid bodies hold the physical properties of an object like
it's mass, and position and velocity of it's center of gravity. They don't have an shape on their own.
They are given a shape by creating collision shapes (cpShape) that point to the body.
Documented so that the Kiwi counter parts will have their documented code also.

cp.Constraint.name: cp.Constraint
cp.Constraint.description: Contains the core functionality that is required by constraints used in Chipmunk.

cp.Shape.name: cp.Shape
cp.Shape.description:
Contains the base shape object which all others extend from. 
The cpShape struct defines the shape of a rigid body.
Opaque collision shape struct. Do not create directly - instead use
PolyShape, CircleShape and SegmentShape.

Documented so that the Kiwi counter parts will have their documented code also.

params.name: body
params.description: The body that this shape should be attached to.

cp.Space.name: cp.Space
cp.Space.description: Basic Unit of Simulation in Chipmunk

Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Body.name: Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Body
Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Body.description:
An extended version of the Chipmunk Body class.
This object has been designed to function with Kiwi Transform Objects and the transformation hierarchy associated with them.

Nice aliases have also been attached :)

Note: Scale on transforms are not taken into account for an objects shape (hitbox). 
But position due to scale is taken into account.

props.name: mass
props.description: The mass of this body.

props.name: i
props.description: Moment of inertia. Used to resolve collisions.

props.name: transform
props.description:
The transform that this body will use to position itself by. 
      If not passed, one is created.

props.name: center
props.description: The location of the bodies centeroid from the transform top left corner. You must either assign both or neither.

props.name: x
props.description: The X location of the centeroid. Defaults to the transforms anchorPointX.

props.name: y
props.description: The Y location of the centeroid. Defaults to the transforms anchorPointY/

props.name: owner
props.description: The owner of this body. Generally assigned to a sprite.

props.name: velocity
props.description: Velocity of the body.

props.name: x
props.description: Velocity of the body on the x-axis.

props.name: y
props.description: Velocity of the body on the y-axis.

props.name: maxVelocity
props.description: Maximum velocity of the body.

props.name: angVelo
props.description: Angular velocity of the body.

props.name: maxAngVelo
props.description: Maximum angular velocity of the body.

Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Joints.Gear.description:
Gear joints constrain the rotational speed of one body to another. 
A ratio of 1.0 will lock the rotation of two bodies together, 
and negative ratios will cause them to spin in opposite directions.

Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Circ.name: Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Circle
Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Circ.description:
Circle shape. 
Good to use for balls, wheels or any other circular collisions.
Requires a body and radius to function.
The body will be at the center of circle (unless you pass a offset).
Technically extends 'cp.CircleShape' but modified it to keep docs nice.

Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Poly.name: Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Poly
Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Shapes.Poly.description:
Used to create polygon hitboxes. 
Polygons have to be convex NOT concave.
Requires a body and a 1D array of vertice coordinates [x1, y1, x2, y2, e.t.c.] 
The vertices need to be positioned around the body. 
Technically extends 'cp.PolyShape' but modified it to keep docs nice.

Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Manager.description:
Create for each Kiwi game using the Chipmunk Physics Plugin.
In charge of creating new spaces for the game, and updating them each frame.

A default space is included and is used by default by components.

Damping rate expressed as the fraction of velocity bodies retain each second.
A value of 0.9 would mean that each body's velocity will drop 10% per second.
classitems.name: damping

classitems.description:
The number of iterations that the space property should update each frame.
The higher this is the more accurate the physics will be, but the more process intensive it will be also.
classitems.name: iterations

classitems.description:
Amount of encouraged penetration between colliding shapes..
Used to reduce oscillating contacts and keep the collision cache warm.
Defaults to 0.1. If you have poor simulation quality,
increase this number as much as possible without allowing visible amounts of overlap.
classitems.name: collisionSlop

classitems.description:
Determines how fast overlapping shapes are pushed apart.
Expressed as a fraction of the error remaining after each second.
Defaults to pow(1.0 - 0.1, 60.0) meaning that Chipmunk fixes 10% of overlap each frame at 60Hz.
classitems.name: collisionBias

classitems.description:
Number of frames that contact information should persist.
Defaults to 3. There is probably never a reason to change this value.
classitems.name: collisionPersistence

classitems.description:
Speed threshold for a body to be considered idle.

classitems.description:
Creates a new body based on the configuration parameters passed and the sprite.

A number of different 'types' of bodies can be created and the type you choose changes the parameters you need to pass.
Also look at 'Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Body' for more parameters you can pass.

- 'box' - Uses the 'Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.createBoxBody' function
- 'circle' - Uses the 'Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.createCircleBody'  function
- 'segment' - Uses the 'Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.createSegmentBody'  function
- 'poly' - Uses the 'Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.createPolyBody'  function
- 'static' - Gets the body from the space. 
- 'custom' - Directly creates a new Kiwi.Plugins.ChipmunkPhysics.Body.

props.description: The mass of the body. If not passed, then one is generated by 'getDefaultMass' method.

props.name: addToSpace
props.description: If the created body should be added to the space or not.

props.name: owner
props.description: The owner of the body. If not passed then the owner is the components owner.

props.name: type
props.description: The type of body that is to be created. This value affects the following parameters that you can pass. Defaults to box.

props.description: 'box' types only. The width of the box. Defaults to box.bound.width if a box component is found. Otherwise 100.

props.name: height
props.description: 'box' types only. The height of the box. Defaults to box.bound.height if a box component is found. Otherwise 100.

props.name: radius
props.description: 'circle' types only. The circles radius. Defaults to half of the box.bounds.height if a box component is found. Otherwise 50.
